article.description: Josh White scored 18 points and North Texas defeated Louisiana-Monroe 74-71 in the regular season finale for both teams on Saturday.
article.headline: North Texas ends regular season with 8th straight win
article.linkText: UNT tops Louisiana-Monroe for 8th straight win
article.story: MONROE, La. -- Josh White scored 18 points and North Texas defeated Louisiana-Monroe 74-71 in the regular season finale for both teams on Saturday. White, who was 13 of 16 from the free throw line, led four players in double figures for the Sun Belt West leading Mean Green (21-8, 13-5). Tristan Thompson chipped in 14 points, and Collin Mangrum and George Odufuwa scored 10 each. Odufuwa, the Sun Belt's leading rebounder at 10.3 per game, finished with 16 boards. The Mean Green led 65-54 with 4:10 remaining, and the Warhawks (11-18, 6-12) went on an 8-1 run, bringing their deficit to four points. Tommie Sykes' layup pulled Louisiana-Monroe within 66-62 with 2:14 to go. However, North Texas went 6-for-6 from the free throw line from that point, sealing its eighth straight win. Dynile Forbes scored 19 and Sykes finished with 12 for the Warhawks, who lost their fourth straight.
